value.value: 第一鰓弓の欠如
absence of the structure of the first arch which contributes to development of mastication muscles, maxilla, mandible, incus, malleus, Meckel's cartilage, trigeminal nerve, and maxillary artery

increased size of the first branchial arch
第二鰓弓の矮小化
reduced size of the second branchial arch
第二鰓弓の欠如

absence of the structure of the second arch which contributes to the development of the stapes, styloid process, hyoid bone, stylohyoid ligament, muscles of facial expression, stapedius muscle, stylohyoid muscle, and lining of the palatine tonsils
鰓弓の矮小化
reduced size of one or more of the branchial arches
第六鰓弓の形態異常

greater than normal concentration of copper in the blood

lower than normal blood concentration of a modified form of hemoglobin with an attached saccharide molecule
糖化ヘモグロビン値上昇

ミネラル血中濃度異常

any anomaly in the concentration in the blood of any naturally occurring, homogeneous inorganic solid substance having a definite chemical composition and highly ordered atomic arrangement that is required for growth and survival
耳介反射の欠如
complete failure to respond to an auditory stimulus by a characteristic ear twitch
驚愕反応消失
failure to respond to variable stimuli, often auditory; usually measured by amplitude of whole body flinch
雌性生殖細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly female germ cells whether they are undifferentiated or fully differentiated
雄性生殖細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of male germ cells whether they are undifferentiated or fully differentiated
曲毛（真ん中くらいで一箇所曲がっていて毛髄に空気を含む毛）の欠損
absence of truncal hairs having a single constriction and bend about midway along the hair shaft, and contain two or more air cells in the medulla
錐毛（千枚通しのようにまっすぐだけど短い毛）の欠損
absence of truncal hairs that are straight, but are shorter than guard hairs, and contain two or more air cells in the medulla
上毛欠如
absence of the long, straight truncal hairs that contain two air cells in the medulla
ジグザグ毛の欠如
absence of the truncal hairs that have two or more sharp bends with diameter constrictions at the bends, and contain one air cell in the medulla
汗腺の欠如
absence of any of the coil glands of the skin that secrete sweat
過剰切歯
more than the usual number of incisors, normally consisting of two pairs, top and bottom, of the long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw

毛包褐色メラニン欠如
yellow pigment is not present in pheomelanosomes of the hair follicle
胎盤の機能障害
reduction in the ability of the placenta to supply nutrients or remove waste
アンジオテンシン前駆体の血中濃度異常
anomaly in the concentration of the serum globulin formed by the liver that is cleaved by renin to form angiotensin I
アンジオテンシン前駆体の血中濃度上昇
greater than normal concentration of the serum globulin formed by the liver that is cleaved by renin to form angiotensin I
アンジオテンシン前駆体の血中濃度低下
less than normal concentration of the serum globulin formed by the liver that is cleaved by renin to form angiotensin I
前庭頸反射の異常
any anomaly in the neural reflex which results from activation of afferents from the vestibular organs and uses neck movements to stabilize the head position in space
精原細胞の形態学的異常
any structural anomaly of the large unspecialized male germ cells that give rise to spermatocytes
精母細胞の形態学的異常
any structural anomaly of male germ cells that through meiosis give rise to spermatids
精子細胞の形態学的異常
any structural anomaly of the male germ cells that without further cell division give rise to mature spermatozoa
肺上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the epithelial layer of the lung
蝸牛の周波数同調の異常

any anomaly in the frequency resolution of the cochlea, normally determined by the passive mechanical properties of the basilar membrane and active feedback from the outer hair cells which detect and amplify sound-induced basilar membrane motions
蝸牛の周波数同調の先鋭化
increase in the sharpness of frequency resolution of the cochlea
体節の欠如
absence of mesodermal clusters that are arranged segmentally along the anterior posterior axis of an embryo
異常Ｔ細胞数
deviation from the normal count of T cells
聴覚累加電位異常

any anomaly in the dc shift in the waveform sustained for the duration of a toneburst stimulus that represents the depolarization of sensory hair cells in the cochlea; positive summating potentials (SPs) reflect activity of basal turn hair cells while negative SPs are derived from hair cell activity in the apical turn; negative SPs tend to be obtained at low frequencies and low intensities of stimulus, while positive SPs are recorded in response to high frequencies and high intensities
前庭内リンパの異常
change in the normal production (volume) or ionic homeostasis of the fluid contained within the vestibule of the inner ear; unlike cochlear endolymph this fluid does not have a high potential
蝸牛内リンパの異常
change in the normal production (volume) or ionic homeostasis of the fluid contained within the cochlea of the inner ear
前庭内リンパのイオン恒常性異常
anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of charged molecules in the vestibular endolymph
髄核の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the jelly-like substance in the middle of the spinal disc which is a remnant of the notochord
髄核の欠如
missing the notochord remnant normally found in the center of the intervertebral disc
椎骨骨端軟骨板の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the lateral cartilaginous centers of ossification; may be found on the lateral, upper, and/or lower surfaces of the vertebrae at different times during development
骨端軟骨板の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the cartilaginous center of ossification on the bones permitting growth of the bone in both directions during development
